to run the server:
npm run dev

The dev server is bound to all interfaces (host: true). Other computers on your network can open the app using the "Network" URL Vite prints (e.g. http://192.168.x.x:5173).

If Stockfish does not load (e.g. CDN blocked), run once to fetch the engine locally:
node scripts/download-stockfish.js

Two FEN / Stockfish flows:
- Top (manual): Position comes from camera or the main FEN input; you click "Apply FEN" then "Get best move". Same engine (stockfish.ts), now uses same local direct-worker loading as the bottom section.
- Bottom (alternate): Its own FEN input; position auto-applies after you stop typing (debounce), and the engine re-evaluates automatically. Uses stockfish-v2.ts (direct worker only).